{"word":"H5988 - עַמִּיאֵל - ʻAmmîyʼêl - am-mee-ale' - Ammiel","slug":"H5988","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עַמִּיאֵל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻAmmîyʼêl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>am-mee-ale'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Ammiel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>עמּיאל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>‛ammı̂y'êl</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>am-mee-ale'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Ammiel = \"my kinsman is God\" <ol><li>the spy from the tribe of Dan who perished in the plague for his evil report</li><li>father of Machir of Lo-debar</li><li>father of Bathsheba; also 'Eliam'</li><li>the 6th son of Obed-edom and doorkeeper of the temple</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H5971\">H5971</a> and <a href=\"#/H410\">H410</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5971\">H5971</a>, <a href=\"#/H5973\">H5973</a>, <a href=\"#/H5978\">H5978</a>, <a href=\"#/H5980\">H5980</a>, <a href=\"#/H5981\">H5981</a>, <a href=\"#/H5983\">H5983</a>, <a href=\"#/H5984\">H5984</a>, <a href=\"#/H5985\">H5985</a>, <a href=\"#/H5989\">H5989</a>, <a href=\"#/H5990\">H5990</a>, <a href=\"#/H5991\">H5991</a>, <a href=\"#/H5992\">H5992</a>, <a href=\"#/H5996\">H5996</a>, <a href=\"#/H6005\">H6005</a>"}]}